CREATE TABLE Player (
    player_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    team_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES SportsTeam(team_id)
);

CREATE TABLE stadium (stadium_id INT PRIMARY KEY, stadium_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, city VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL)</t><stat>insert into team (team_id, team_name, sport) select 1, 'team a', 'football'</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE match (match_id INT PRIMARY KEY, match_date DATE NOT NULL, team1_id INT NOT NULL, team2_id INT NOT NULL) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE tournament (tournament_id INT PRIMARY KEY, tournament_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)

CREATE TABLE player (player_id INT PRIMARY KEY, player_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, team_id INT NOT NULL, age INT) REFERENCES team(team_id)

CREATE TABLE stadium (stadium_id INT PRIMARY KEY, stadium_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, city VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL)</t><stat>insert into stadium (stadium_id, stadium_name, city) select 3, 'stadium z', 'city x'</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE tournament (tournament_id INT PRIMARY KEY, tournament_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, sport VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL)
